snippet.textDisplay: Farida Khanum is a Pakistani Classical Singer from the Punjab.She was born in Calcutta in 1935, but her family origins are from Amritsar.Her family moved to Pakistan after partition of India in 1947.Farida Khanum gave her first public concert in 1950 and then joined Radio Pakistan where she courted fame and fortune.[1] She became a star when Pakistan’s president Ayub Khan invited her to a public recital in the 1960s.
snippet.textOriginal: Farida Khanum is a Pakistani Classical Singer from the Punjab.She was born in Calcutta in 1935, but her family origins are from Amritsar.Her family moved to Pakistan after partition of India in 1947.Farida Khanum gave her first public concert in 1950 and then joined Radio Pakistan where she courted fame and fortune.[1] She became a star when Pakistan’s president Ayub Khan invited her to a public recital in the 1960s.
